post_text:
Cheney Middle School football is suspending team activity until 9/14. This decision was under direction of the Sedgwick County Health Department and Covid 19 circumstances. This is not an easy or desired situation, but in this time we don't get to choose the timing and circumstances of changes being put in our path.

Games scheduled for 9/3, 9/10 and 9/14 will not be played. We will attempt to modify the schedule and play as many games as we can when we are able to resume. We will continue to do what we can to keep our kids involved in school and activities as much as possible using the data and guidance that we are given.

post_text:
Following is an update on the short term outlook for schools in Kansas:

It is recommended that all Kansas schools close for this week through next Sunday the 22nd. Cheney is on Spring Break so we are not currently affected by the closure, but 42% of schools in the state are not on Spring Break.

Our facilities will remain empty this week as our maintenance and custodial staff are doing a deep clean.

We are to have a longer term outlook/plan presented on Thursday from KDHE and KSDE.

As we learn more, we will provide updates. During our time away we ask that everyone do their part by practicing good hygiene and social distancing measures.

post_text: Cheney FFA Community Service
shared_text:
Stacy Bolinger DeVore is with Kayla Young.
February 25 at 6:46 PM ·

This week is National FFA Week! The Cheney FFA Chapter decided to do a community service project. We were able to get a Spring semester Grant from National FFA for $1200. Our Chapter voted to add $1000 from their Blue and Gold Sales. The project that was chosen was the Cheney Senior Citizen Center remodel. The first step was to move everything from the main floor to the basement. They removed old trim, crown molding, wall tiles, old carpet, painted trim, ceiling, and walls, and tomorrow will help with the flooring. It has been a great experience working with the City of Cheney and Carla Ewy! BTW the City of Cheney is doing most of the work, but we are getting to help as much as possible.
